20
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:41,544
Hello? Is anyone there?

21
00:01:41,544 --> 00:01:43,244
- Hello. 
 - Hello.

22
00:01:43,244 --> 00:01:45,464
- Are you Jiang?
- Yeah.

23
00:01:45,464 --> 00:01:47,924
I'm Ye Meng, a friend of Cheng Kai Ran.

24
00:01:47,924 --> 00:01:51,020
I see. Then we're family here. Sit.

25
00:01:53,760 --> 00:02:00,144
I'd like to ask about an antique.
Have you seen this thumb ring?

26
00:02:05,684 --> 00:02:10,444
This wasn't sold here, but it looks familiar.

27
00:02:14,704 --> 00:02:17,928
I remember now. A few years ago,

28
00:02:17,928 --> 00:02:22,164
a middle-aged man came to me
to appraise this thumb ring.

29
00:02:22,164 --> 00:02:26,064
It was top-quality. So I made several offers.

30
00:02:26,064 --> 00:02:29,204
But he wouldn't sell it.

31
00:02:30,124 --> 00:02:33,964
Do you know his name
or have his contact information?

32
00:02:34,504 --> 00:02:39,624
Sorry, I only knew that he wasn't local
and was on a business trip from Jiangbei.

33
00:02:43,264 --> 00:02:46,124
It's okay. Could you add me on WeChat?

34
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:49,570
- Alright.
- Text me if you recall anything.

35
00:02:50,284 --> 00:02:53,544
- Okay. Don't mention it.
- Thank you. Sorry for the trouble. See you.

36
00:02:53,544 --> 00:02:55,264
- Alright. 
- Okay. Thanks.

37
00:02:55,264 --> 00:02:57,644
- Bye. 
- Bye.

38
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:10,604
Could that seller be the man
who visited my mom years ago?

39
00:03:11,684 --> 00:03:14,564
There is a chance. Here's what we'll do.

40
00:03:14,564 --> 00:03:18,200
I'll ask my friends in Jiangbei to ask around.

41
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:21,724
I'll also contact my friend there.

42
00:03:21,724 --> 00:03:25,024
Your "friend" in Jiangbei? Your ex-boss?

43
00:03:25,024 --> 00:03:28,864
No. Tai Ming Xiao, my former colleague.

44
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:34,900
You sound strange. Are you jealous?

45
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,404
Why would I be jealous?

46
00:03:36,404 --> 00:03:37,964
Good that you're not.

47
00:03:37,964 --> 00:03:43,164
After all, he's been
my handsome and kind partner for years.

48
00:03:43,164 --> 00:03:46,084
There's nothing I can do even if you're jealous.

49
00:03:46,084 --> 00:03:47,544
What kind of partner is he?

50
00:03:47,544 --> 00:03:51,004
Tai Ming Xiao? My late-night snack buddy.

51
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:56,600
Sounds like you had a lot of fun in Jiangbei.
You even had a "partner".

52
00:03:57,984 --> 00:04:01,284
Just admit you're jealous.
Longing for a relationship isn't shameful.

53
00:04:01,284 --> 00:04:03,744
I said I'm not jealous.

54
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:05,644
Really?

55
00:04:07,204 --> 00:04:10,684
After the Spring Festival comes spring.

56
00:04:10,684 --> 00:04:14,444
Even Ping An is going out,
looking for girlfriends every day.

57
00:04:14,444 --> 00:04:16,444
Do you really want to stay single forever?

58
00:04:16,444 --> 00:04:20,904
Maybe Ping An is going out to find me a job.

59
00:04:20,904 --> 00:04:27,004
I don't believe it. Let's bet.
He's definitely looking for a girlfriend.

60
00:04:27,004 --> 00:04:29,664
Ping An can't talk. How do we bet?

61
00:04:29,664 --> 00:04:31,264
I have an idea.

62
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,400
Done.

63
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:41,400
You really stoop to anything to win.

64
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:44,484
You even installed a dashcam on Ping An.

65
00:04:44,484 --> 00:04:50,484
Never underestimate a woman's competitiveness
and her desire to conquer.

66
00:04:52,164 --> 00:04:54,064
What's the wager?

67
00:04:54,604 --> 00:04:59,884
If you lose, admit you were jealous earlier

68
00:04:59,884 --> 00:05:02,844
and that you want a relationship.

69
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,934
Deal.

70
00:05:04,934 --> 00:05:08,504
Poor Ping An,

71
00:05:08,504 --> 00:05:10,484
getting monitored while dating.

72
00:05:10,484 --> 00:05:13,304
Remember to blur his girlfriend's face.

73
00:05:13,304 --> 00:05:15,404
You're already giving up, young man?

74
00:05:15,404 --> 00:05:18,724
What if Ping An really is job-hunting?

75
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:23,044
Do you have a problem with me today?

76
00:05:23,044 --> 00:05:28,164
No, it just amuses me to tease you.

77
00:05:31,284 --> 00:05:35,784
Your ears look so red.

78
00:05:35,784 --> 00:05:38,324
It's from the cold.

79
00:05:38,324 --> 00:05:40,784
Cold? I'm wearing shorts and I'm fine.

80
00:05:40,784 --> 00:05:42,464
So much vanity.

81
00:05:42,464 --> 00:05:45,524
- How does this thing work? 
 - I don't know.

82
00:05:45,524 --> 00:05:49,264
Wait, are you trying to weasel out?

83
00:05:49,264 --> 00:05:51,260
...

84
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:56,344
You're too kind, Mr. Wang.
We'll need your support next year, too.

85
00:05:56,344 --> 00:05:57,664
Happy New Year.

86
00:05:57,664 --> 00:05:59,284
I wasn't being kind.

87
00:05:59,284 --> 00:06:00,824
Shut up.

88
00:06:00,824 --> 00:06:04,884
Happy New Year, Mr. Li.
Have you received the health supplements?

89
00:06:04,884 --> 00:06:06,104
Remember to take them.

90
00:06:06,104 --> 00:06:08,064
No, I haven't. Where did you send them?

91
00:06:08,064 --> 00:06:10,944
Work more and talk less. I could've made
twice the dumplings you made.

92
00:06:10,944 --> 00:06:14,104
Finish wrapping what's in your hands first.

93
00:06:14,104 --> 00:06:16,864
Meng, what filling do you want?

94
00:06:16,864 --> 00:06:19,204
Peanut filling.

95
00:06:19,204 --> 00:06:21,424
I'm video-calling my dad.

96
00:06:21,424 --> 00:06:25,324
Really? Let me see.

97
00:06:25,324 --> 00:06:27,604
- Brother.
- Brother.

98
00:06:27,604 --> 00:06:29,404
Dad, did you have dumplings?

99
00:06:29,404 --> 00:06:32,124
I'll cook them now. They gave us some at work.

100
00:06:32,124 --> 00:06:38,324
Are you the only worker at the bank?
Why are you staying over every Spring Festival?

101
00:06:38,324 --> 00:06:40,924
Mom, I won't procrastinate this time.

102
00:06:40,924 --> 00:06:44,864
I'll handle the handover after the festival
and we'll meet soon.

103
00:06:44,864 --> 00:06:48,384
Really? It's settled then. We'll be waiting.

104
00:06:48,384 --> 00:06:51,324
Alright. Meng.

105
00:06:51,324 --> 00:06:54,604
I have some things to do.
Take care of your grandma and aunts.

106
00:06:54,604 --> 00:06:56,704
- Okay. 
 - Take care of yourself.

107
00:06:56,704 --> 00:06:59,464
- Happy New Year!
- Happy New Year!

108
00:06:59,464 --> 00:07:02,424
- Bye.
- Bye.

109
00:07:02,424 --> 00:07:05,284
He's funny. Who's taking care of whom?

110
00:07:05,284 --> 00:07:10,084
They're finally showing some humanity
and letting your dad return to his family.

111
00:07:10,084 --> 00:07:12,404
And you should move back, too.

112
00:07:12,404 --> 00:07:15,564
We have so many spare rooms at home.

113
00:07:15,564 --> 00:07:19,084
The old house is decaying without tenants.

114
00:07:19,084 --> 00:07:23,524
Grandma always said that houses need residents.

115
00:07:23,524 --> 00:07:26,244
Did I say that?

116
00:07:26,244 --> 00:07:30,484
Grandma, what are you making?
I asked for peanut filling.

117
00:07:30,484 --> 00:07:34,444
Right, make her some peanut filling.

118
00:07:35,004 --> 00:07:37,164
We're out of peanut butter.

119
00:07:37,164 --> 00:07:39,364
- Well... 
 - I'll go buy some.

120
00:07:39,364 --> 00:07:42,504
You're going? Don't take too long.

121
00:07:42,504 --> 00:07:44,824
Mom, look at her slacking off, doing nothing.

122
00:07:44,824 --> 00:07:46,164
Me? Slacking off?

123
00:07:46,164 --> 00:07:48,024
- Hurry up.
- Have you no conscience?

124
00:07:48,024 --> 00:07:52,504
You two miss each other when apart,
but fight when you meet.

125
00:07:55,824 --> 00:07:57,644
- How much per jin?
- Ten yuan.

126
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:59,284
- I'll take two jin then.
- Okay.

127
00:07:59,284 --> 00:08:01,284
Give me some extra.

128
00:08:08,644 --> 00:08:10,664
What are you doing?

129
00:08:10,664 --> 00:08:15,364
I know where you hide your keys now.
I'll sneak in tonight.

130
00:08:17,484 --> 00:08:19,044
Why are you here?

131
00:08:19,044 --> 00:08:24,944
Putting up couplets. Your house looks bare
without any holiday spirit.

132
00:08:24,944 --> 00:08:27,384
- That's unnecessary. 
 - Don't be ridiculous.

133
00:08:27,384 --> 00:08:31,604
Come on, tall guy.
Put up the horizontal scroll.

134
00:08:34,004 --> 00:08:37,524
Check if these are aligned.

135
00:08:37,524 --> 00:08:40,464
- A bit lower. 
 - Lower?

136
00:08:40,464 --> 00:08:43,064
- You sure? 
 - Yeah.

137
00:08:46,684 --> 00:08:47,884
 

138
00:08:47,884 --> 00:08:49,804
What about this one?

139
00:08:49,804 --> 00:08:51,944
- A bit to the right.
- Okay.

140
00:08:51,944 --> 00:08:54,064
A bit to the left.

141
00:08:54,064 --> 00:08:56,364
I've already pasted it.

142
00:08:56,924 --> 00:08:59,264
Fine.

143
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:03,564
Hello? I just left. Be there in 15 minutes.

144
00:09:03,564 --> 00:09:05,864
Keep the good tiles.

145
00:09:05,864 --> 00:09:10,284
Don't come over. We're having fun playing mahjong.

146
00:09:10,284 --> 00:09:12,624
- One Bamboo.
- Didn't you ask for dumplings?

147
00:09:12,624 --> 00:09:17,544
I had some at the hospital.
We ordered takeout for the celebration.

148
00:09:17,544 --> 00:09:22,724
Since you're bored at home,
I arranged something for you.

149
00:09:22,724 --> 00:09:24,964
What did you arrange?

150
00:09:25,624 --> 00:09:30,124
Go to Ye Meng's home for the Spring Festival.

151
00:09:30,124 --> 00:09:31,844
Here we go. Five Dots.

152
00:09:31,844 --> 00:09:35,164
That's it. We're playing mahjong. I'm winning.

153
00:09:35,164 --> 00:09:36,964
No need, I...

154
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:42,484
I took Granny's red envelope.
I'm taking you home by force if needed.

155
00:09:44,404 --> 00:09:47,844
Let's get some groceries then.

156
00:09:47,844 --> 00:09:49,784
That's what I'm up to.

157
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:54,964
Self-drawn win.

158
00:09:54,964 --> 00:09:56,704
So lucky.

159
00:09:56,704 --> 00:09:59,044
Bed No. 3. Stop playing.

160
00:09:59,044 --> 00:10:02,064
I'm back. Are the dumplings ready?

161
00:10:02,064 --> 00:10:06,004
Meng, I didn't know we're taking orders.
Where's the peanut butter?

162
00:10:06,004 --> 00:10:07,684
What took you so long?

163
00:10:07,684 --> 00:10:13,064
Okay, let's meet after the festival.

164
00:10:14,684 --> 00:10:16,504
Goodbye, Mr. Li. We have a guest.

165
00:10:16,504 --> 00:10:19,724
Who's this?

166
00:10:20,424 --> 00:10:21,664
This is...?

167
00:10:21,664 --> 00:10:24,624
Granny, Auntie, Second Aunt,
Third Aunt, nice to meet you.

168
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:25,904
Hello.

169
00:10:25,904 --> 00:10:30,524
He's my friend. His family's away,
so I brought him here.

170
00:10:30,524 --> 00:10:32,524
Welcome.

171
00:10:33,324 --> 00:10:37,064
Friend? What kind of friend?

172
00:10:37,064 --> 00:10:38,604
Boyfriend?

173
00:10:38,604 --> 00:10:40,664
What do you do?

174
00:10:40,664 --> 00:10:43,564
No, just regular friends for now.

175
00:10:43,564 --> 00:10:46,844
Be nice, okay? Don't scare him away.

176
00:10:46,844 --> 00:10:52,144
Let's welcome Meng's friend. Come with Granny.

177
00:10:52,144 --> 00:10:56,964
Come in. What a tall young man.

178
00:10:56,964 --> 00:10:58,384
Who is he?

179
00:10:58,384 --> 00:11:00,124
Sister.

180
00:11:00,124 --> 00:11:03,100
What do you want?

181
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:05,384
- Get some water. 
 - Why does he look familiar?

182
00:11:05,384 --> 00:11:09,864
- That makes sense. 
 - What do you mean? Where did you meet?

183
00:11:09,864 --> 00:11:13,364
- What's your surname? 
 - My surname is Li. Just call me Li.

184
00:11:13,364 --> 00:11:14,804
- Li. 
 - Good surname.

185
00:11:14,804 --> 00:11:18,244
Many of my wealthy clients have that surname.

186
00:11:18,244 --> 00:11:20,784
- How old are you? 
 - Twenty-seven.

187
00:11:20,784 --> 00:11:23,324
Twenty-seven? Two years younger than Meng.

188
00:11:23,324 --> 00:11:26,244
That's fine. I like younger men.

189
00:11:26,244 --> 00:11:28,124
Boy-crazy.

190
00:11:28,124 --> 00:11:30,044
What do you do?

191
00:11:30,044 --> 00:11:32,804
I have no stable job. I do a bit of everything.

192
00:11:32,804 --> 00:11:37,084
So you're versatile. Good, as long as
you can take care of Meng.

193
00:11:37,084 --> 00:11:42,084
Honestly, money isn't important.
As long as you two are happy.

194
00:11:42,084 --> 00:11:46,424
Why do you look so familiar?
I think I've seen you somewhere.

195
00:11:46,424 --> 00:11:51,464
- Right, Mom? That was what I thought. 
 - You've met before. At the old house.

196
00:11:53,484 --> 00:11:55,684
The repairman.

197
00:11:55,684 --> 00:12:00,364
Grandma, I was joking back then.
He's Mrs. Tou's grandson.

198
00:12:00,364 --> 00:12:04,024
Remember when our roof was leaking?
He came to help fix it.

199
00:12:04,024 --> 00:12:06,324
You're Tou Ju Hua's grandson?

200
00:12:06,324 --> 00:12:08,404
Yes.

201
00:12:08,404 --> 00:12:11,624
No wonder you're not coming home.
So you're dating someone.

202
00:12:11,624 --> 00:12:13,524
- Not yet.
- Li.

203
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:16,724
- What do your parents--
- Do for work?

204
00:12:19,024 --> 00:12:23,284
My dad passed away. I live with my grandma now.

205
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:24,424
I'm sorry.

206
00:12:24,424 --> 00:12:26,124
It's okay.

207
00:12:27,884 --> 00:12:29,984
I'm starving. Are the dumplings ready?

208
00:12:29,984 --> 00:12:31,204
I forgot it...

209
00:12:31,204 --> 00:12:34,384
- Weren't you making calls?
- Let me prepare your red envelope.

210
00:12:34,384 --> 00:12:36,484
- No need, Granny.
- Let's eat. The New Year is coming.

211
00:12:36,484 --> 00:12:38,284
What's wrong?

212
00:12:40,724 --> 00:12:45,844
Well, go ahead and talk. Have some melon seeds.

213
00:12:46,564 --> 00:12:48,924
- Have some peanuts.
- I hope they didn't scare you.

214
00:12:48,924 --> 00:12:50,524
Not at all.

215
00:12:51,924 --> 00:12:54,324
- Thank you. 
 - Let me peel an orange for you.

216
00:12:54,324 --> 00:12:56,124
No need.

217
00:12:58,584 --> 00:13:00,636
It's Chinese New Year's Eve.

218
00:13:00,636 --> 00:13:03,444
May our new year

219
00:13:03,444 --> 00:13:08,724
be filled with togetherness,
smooth sailing, and happiness.

220
00:13:08,724 --> 00:13:10,624
You've worked hard.

221
00:13:11,804 --> 00:13:14,844
Nice dumplings. Try some.

222
00:13:14,844 --> 00:13:17,564
It's nice. Have more.

223
00:13:17,564 --> 00:13:19,264
Alright then. Try it.

224
00:13:19,264 --> 00:13:21,624
- I toast you. 
 - I'll drink with you.

225
00:13:21,624 --> 00:13:24,424
- Toast to you.
- Mom, I toast to you.

226
00:13:24,424 --> 00:13:27,004
That's enough. My plate's already full.

227
00:13:27,004 --> 00:13:30,844
- Dig in.
- I've got more here.

228
00:13:30,844 --> 00:13:33,804
Now, I'll be handing out red envelopes.

229
00:13:33,804 --> 00:13:35,664
I've been waiting for it.

230
00:13:35,664 --> 00:13:37,844
- Meng.
- What's that got to do with you?

231
00:13:37,844 --> 00:13:39,384
Me first.

232
00:13:39,384 --> 00:13:42,584
- Everyone gets one. 
 - Starting with the youngest.

233
00:13:42,584 --> 00:13:44,804
Let me see.

234
00:14:26,364 --> 00:14:31,244
All my family loves good-looking people.
They're just excited to see you.

235
00:14:31,244 --> 00:14:35,484
It means that they approve of you, right?

236
00:14:36,404 --> 00:14:42,764
Actually, I find your family quite lovely,
completely different from what I imagined.

237
00:14:42,764 --> 00:14:48,464
Though I suppose only a family like that
can raise a girl like you.

238
00:14:48,464 --> 00:14:51,484
So you've been imagining things.

239
00:14:52,064 --> 00:14:55,604
It's cold. Go upstairs.
I'm going to visit my grandma.

240
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:58,684
Would you like to
set off fireworks with me afterward?

241
00:14:58,684 --> 00:15:03,904
I prepared so many fireworks for your birthday.
They're still in the warehouse.

242
00:15:07,064 --> 00:15:10,160
We'll see. I'll contact you later.

243
00:15:10,704 --> 00:15:12,904
I'm off.

244
00:15:17,824 --> 00:15:19,524
Li Jin Yu.

245
00:15:26,324 --> 00:15:28,324
Happy New Year.

246
00:15:39,344 --> 00:15:41,160
I'm sorry.

247
00:15:41,704 --> 00:15:43,604
What did you say?

248
00:15:45,324 --> 00:15:49,390
I said, Happy New Year. Go up now.

249
00:15:50,064 --> 00:15:51,664
Bye.

250
00:15:54,024 --> 00:15:55,624
Bye.

251
